						<summary>

						<p>On a fourth pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 27: 933-34 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 180 sheep by Eḻuvaṉ Vaḍukaṉ, for burning two perpetual lamps to the deity Tirumaṟaikkāṭṭu-mahādēva, with one <hi rend="italic">uri</hi> of ghee daily by the measure called Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
